    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've put together:\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**5 files to create/modify** — all following patterns already established by the `userAgent` / `next/server` implementation:\n\n### Files\n\n| Action | Path |\n|--------|------|\n| Create | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| Create | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| Create | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| Modify | `packages/next/package.json` |\n| Create | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n\n1. **`geo.ts`** — Exports `Geo` interface + four functions. Header priority: `x-vercel-ip-country` takes precedence over `cf-ipcountry`. `country` (human-readable) is derived from `countryCode` via a `COUNTRY_NAMES` map. The `|| undefined` pattern (not `|| null`) converts missing headers to `undefined` to match TypeScript optional fields. Private `toRad()` helper for Haversine math.\n\n2. **`geo.js`** — Exact pattern of `server.js`: build a `geoExports` object, `module.exports = geoExports`, then re-assign each export on `exports.xxx` for named ESM import compatibility.\n\n3. **`geo.d.ts`** — Exact pattern of `server.d.ts`: one `export { ... } from 'next/dist/...'` per symbol, plus `export type { Geo }`.\n\n4. **`package.json`** — Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical: f → **g** → router...).\n\n5. **`geo.test.ts`** — Jest tests (matching the `adapters/headers.test.ts` style) covering: full Vercel header extraction, missing headers → all `undefined`, Cloudflare fallback, Vercel-over-CF priority, unknown country code → `undefined` country, all 10 `COUNTRY_NAMES` entries, `isInRegion` matching/non-matching/case-insensitive/undefined, NY→London distance (~5570 km ±50 km tolerance), and zero-distance same-point.\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types                      # type check (~10s)\npnpm test-unit .../geo.test.ts                # unit tests\npnpm --filter=next build                      # full build\nnode -e \"console.log(Object.keys(require('./packages/next/geo.js')))\"  # smoke test\n```",
